attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, BuildID[sha1]=e4b25d2e6fb4c0c7defa15f6417dabd5e728cbed, for FreeBSD 10.4, FreeBSD-style, not stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a specialized piece of ransomware, identified by its internal strings and behavior as part of the 'Interlock' family. It utilizes a multi-threaded encryption engine to perform recursive filesystem traversal and encrypt user data. It implements a hybrid encryption scheme using the LibTomCrypt library, employing AES (CBC mode) for file content and RSA for encrypting the per-file symmetric keys. Encrypted files are renamed with the '.interlock' extension. The malware drops a ransom note named '/!__README__!.txt' containing extortion language and a Tor-based contact URL (kmh6vkyfyjjzfllm3ix72aqaid.onion). It also includes features for self-deletion and directory exclusion to avoid system instability during the encryption process.
